<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="be80aca6-6a70-5135-9f01-f4ebb242bee4" activityNameId="cb6406bc-ed2a-47ce-a520-2ede26457947" parentActivityId="b8257905-db66-569d-be46-c780e386992c" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">bisphenol A production, powder</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">diphenylolpropane</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">bisphenol A sodium salt</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">2,2-bis(4-hydroxyphenyl)propane</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">4,4'-dihydroxy-2,2-diphenylpropane</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">bisphenol A</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">bisphenol A disodium salt</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of bisphenol A powder. The raw materials and chemicals used for production are included, as well as estimated emissions to air and water from production (incomplete), and estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant (approximation). Solid wastes are omitted.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of solid bisphenol A by catalysed condensation of phenol and acetone. Similarly to other bisphenols, bisphenol A is a colourless and odourless solid at room temperature. Bisphenol A is almost insoluble in water but readily soluble in polar medias, i.e. ethers or alcohols (Buysch 2000).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Bisphenol A is mainly used for the production of high grade plastics.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This dataset is based on stoechiometric calculations as well as approximations using data from a large chemical chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Buysch H.-J. (2000) Phenol Derivatives - 4. Bisphenols (Bishydroxyarylal-kanes). In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Sixth Edition, June-2001 Electronic Release (ed. Häussinger P., Leitgeb P. and Schmücker B.), 6 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version un-der: http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/ueic/ull_search_fs.html.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Production by catalysed condensation of phenol and acetone with a yield of 98%. The inventory is based on stoechiometric calculations from the following equation: 2C6H6O + C3H6O -&gt; C15H16O2 + H2O.The emissions to air (0.2 wt% of raw material input) and water were estimated using mass balance. Treatment of the waste water in an internal waste water treatment plant is assumed.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Date of published literature. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
